title: What did Doctor Who fans think of Maisie Williams' debut?
text:
What did Doctor Who fans think of Maisie Williams' debut? What did Doctor Who fans think of Maisie Williams' debut? 
Press Association 2014 / / National Entertainment News Share 
Fierce warrior, social media superstar, spokesperson for a generation and now Doctor Who’s new best pal, is there anything Maisie Williams can’t do? 
The 18-year-old actress joined Clara and the Doctor on their adventures in the much-loved sci-fi drama in an episode entitled The Girl Who Died. (Danny Moloshok/AP) 
Her character, Ashildr, is a young girl in a Viking village where the warriors have all been killed. After Ashildr messes with a dangerous species of warrior aliens, the Doctor and Clara have just hours to turn farmers into fighters and defend the village. 
So, what did the Doctor Who fans make of her appearance? 
Maisie fans (Maisans? Fansies?) were quick to commend the fiery actress on her performance. #DoctorWho I love Maisie Williams she is such a Talent for one so young 
— Optimistic Prime (@Headingley72) October 17, 2015 
The excitement got a bit too much for some of us. THERE ARE BOTH JENNA COLEMAN AND MAISIE WILLIAMS ON MY LAPTOP SCREEN AAHHH. #DoctorWho #9×05 
— Nini Lannister (@laninister) October 17, 2015 
There was plenty of speculation flying around Twitter about the true identity of Asildr, The Girl Who Died. If Maisie Williams is 'The Girl Who Died', is she gonna be immortal? The Doctor's daughter? Granddaughter? River? #DoctorWho
